### ============================================
### Simple Blog MERN — API Test Requests
### VS Code REST Client Extension Required
### ============================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@authToken = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE


### ──────────────────────────────────────────
### HEALTH CHECK
### ──────────────────────────────────────────

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### ──────────────────────────────────────────
### AUTH ROUTES
### ──────────────────────────────────────────

### Register — Normal User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "johndoe",
  "email": "johndoe@example.com",
  "password": "Test1234"
}

###

### Register — Admin User (email must match ADMIN_EMAIL in .env)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "adminuser",
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "Admin1234"
}

###

### Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "Admin1234"
}

###

### Get Current User (Auth Required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────
### POST ROUTES
### ──────────────────────────────────────────

### Create Post (Auth + Admin Required)
POST {{baseUrl}}/posts
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Getting Started with React",
  "content": "React is a popular JavaScript library for building user interfaces. It was developed by Facebook and has become one of the most widely used frontend frameworks in the industry.",
  "category": "technology",
  "tags": ["react", "javascript", "frontend"]
}

###

### Get All Posts (Public — Default Pagination)
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts

###

### Get All Posts — With Pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts?page=1&limit=6

###

### Get All Posts — Filter by Category
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts?category=technology

###

### Get All Posts — Filter by Tag
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts?tag=react

###

### Get All Posts — Search by Title
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts?search=react

###

### Get All Posts — Combined Filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts?page=1&limit=6&category=technology&search=react

###

### Get Post by Slug (Public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts/getting-started-with-react

###

### Update Post (Auth + Admin Required)
### Replace :id with actual MongoDB ObjectId
PUT {{baseUrl}}/posts/:id
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Getting Started with React — Updated",
  "content": "React is a powerful JavaScript library for building modern, interactive user interfaces. Originally developed by Facebook, it continues to be a cornerstone of frontend development.",
  "tags": ["react", "javascript", "frontend", "web"]
}

###

### Delete Post (Auth + Admin Required)
### Replace :id with actual MongoDB ObjectId
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/posts/:id
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────
### UPLOAD ROUTE
### ──────────────────────────────────────────

### Upload Image (Auth + Admin Required)
### Replace file path with an actual image on your system
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary

------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="test-image.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test-image.jpg
------FormBoundary--

### ──────────────────────────────────────────
### ERROR CASE TESTS
### ──────────────────────────────────────────

### Register — Missing Fields (Should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "incomplete"
}

###

### Login — Wrong Password (Should return 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### Get Me — No Token (Should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me

###

### Create Post — No Token (Should return 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Unauthorized Post",
  "content": "This should fail without a token.",
  "category": "test"
}

###

### Get Post — Invalid Slug (Should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts/non-existent-slug-12345
